# Group Audiobooks

## Audiobooks By Id [/audiobooks/{id}{?market}]

+ Parameters
    + id (string, required)

        + Sample: 7iHfbu1YPACw6oZPAFJtqe

### getanaudiobook [GET]
Get Spotify catalog information for a single audiobook. Audiobooks are only available within the US, UK, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand and Australia markets.
+ Parameters
    + market (string, optional)

        + Sample: ES

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        An Audiobook

    + Attributes (AudiobookObject)



+ Response 400 (application/json)

        The request contains malformed data in path, query parameters, or body.

    + Attributes (BadRequest1)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user revoked a token or
the access token has expired. You should re-authenticate the user.

    + Attributes (Unauthorized1)



+ Response 403 (application/json)

        Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired
timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

    + Attributes (Forbidden1)



+ Response 404 (application/json)

        The requested resource cannot be found.

    + Attributes (NotFound1)



+ Response 429 (application/json)

        The app has exceeded its rate limits.

    + Attributes (TooManyRequests1)




## Audiobooks [/audiobooks{?ids,market}]

### getmultipleaudiobooks [GET]
Get Spotify catalog information for several audiobooks identified by their Spotify IDs. Audiobooks are only available within the US, UK, Canada, Ireland, New Zealand and Australia markets.
+ Parameters
    + ids (string, required)

        + Sample: 18yVqkdbdRvS24c0Ilj2ci,1HGw3J3NxZO1TP1BTtVhpZ,7iHfbu1YPACw6oZPAFJtqe
    + market (string, optional)

        + Sample: ES

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        A set of audiobooks. If one of the requested audiobooks is unavailable then you'll find a `null` item in the `audiobooks` array where the audiobook object would otherwise be.

    + Attributes (ManyAudiobooks)



+ Response 401 (application/json)

        Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user revoked a token or
the access token has expired. You should re-authenticate the user.

    + Attributes (Unauthorized1)



+ Response 403 (application/json)

        Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired
timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

    + Attributes (Forbidden1)



+ Response 429 (application/json)

        The app has exceeded its rate limits.

    + Attributes (TooManyRequests1)




