+ `width`: `300` (number, required, nullable) - The image width in pixels.


## ExplicitContentSettingsObject (object)


### Properties
+ `filter_enabled` (boolean, optional) - When `true`, indicates that explicit content should not be played.
+ `filter_locked` (boolean, optional) - When `true`, indicates that the explicit content setting is locked and can't be changed by the user.


## CurrentlyPlayingObject (object)


### Properties
+ `context` (ContextObject, optional) - A Context Object. Can be `null`.
+ `timestamp` (number, optional) - Unix Millisecond Timestamp when data was fetched
+ `progress_ms` (number, optional) - Progress into the currently playing track or episode. Can be `null`.
+ `is_playing` (boolean, optional) - If something is currently playing, return `true`.
+ `item` (string, optional) - The currently playing track or episode. Can be `null`.
+ `currently_playing_type` (string, optional) - The object type of the currently playing item. Can be one of `track`, `episode`, `ad` or `unknown`.
+ `actions` (DisallowsObject, optional) - Allows to update the user interface based on which playback actions are available within the current context.


## SavedAudiobookObject (object)


### Properties
+ `added_at` (string, optional)

    The date and time the audiobook was saved
    Timestamps are returned in ISO 8601 format as Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) with a zero offset: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ.
    If the time is imprecise (for example, the date/time of an album release), an additional field indicates the precision; see for example, release_date in an album object.

+ `audiobook` (AudiobookObject, optional) - Information about the audiobook.


## PagingSavedAudiobookObject (object)


### Properties
+ `href`: `https://api.spotify.com/v1/me/shows?offset=0&limit=20` (string, required) - A link to the Web API endpoint returning the full result of the request
+ `limit`: `20` (number, required) - The maximum number of items in the response (as set in the query or by default).
+ `next`: `https://api.spotify.com/v1/me/shows?offset=1&limit=1` (string, required, nullable) - URL to the next page of items. ( `null` if none)
+ `offset`: `0` (number, required) - The offset of the items returned (as set in the query or by default)
+ `previous`: `https://api.spotify.com/v1/me/shows?offset=1&limit=1` (string, required, nullable) - URL to the previous page of items. ( `null` if none)
+ `total`: `4` (number, required) - The total number of items available to return.
+ `items` (array[SavedAudiobookObject], required) 


